BaN2 crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Ba(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to ten equivalent N(1) atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)–N(1) bond distances ranging from 2.67–3.11 Å. N(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Ba(1) and one N(1) atom. The N(1)–N(1) bond length is 1.23 Å.
LuTlSe2 is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R-3m space group. Lu(1) is bonded to six equivalent Se(1) atoms to form LuSe6 octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Tl(1)Se6 octahedra, edges with six equivalent Lu(1)Se6 octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Tl(1)Se6 octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 11°. All Lu(1)–Se(1) bond lengths are 2.84 Å. Tl(1) is bonded to six equivalent Se(1) atoms to form distorted TlSe6 octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Lu(1)Se6 octahedra, edges with six equivalent Lu(1)Se6 octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Tl(1)Se6 octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 11°. All Tl(1)–Se(1) bond lengths are 3.33 Å. Se(1) is bonded to three equivalent Lu(1) and three equivalent Tl(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SeLu3Tl3 octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.
AuDy is alpha-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Dy(1) is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to seven equivalent Au(1) atoms. There are a spread of Dy(1)–Au(1) bond distances ranging from 3.01–3.11 Å. Au(1) is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to seven equivalent Dy(1) atoms.
NbInS2 crystallizes in the hexagonal P-6m2 space group. Nb(1) is bonded to six equivalent S(1) atoms to form distorted edge-sharing NbS6 pentagonal pyramids. All Nb(1)–S(1) bond lengths are 2.49 Å. In(1) is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent S(1) atoms. Both In(1)–S(1) bond lengths are 2.84 Å. S(1) is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to three equivalent Nb(1) and one In(1) atom.
SmSbTe is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Sm(1) is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sb(1) and five equivalent Te(1) atoms. All Sm(1)–Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.39 Å. There are four shorter (3.21 Å) and one longer (3.29 Å) Sm(1)–Te(1) bond length. Sb(1) is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sm(1) and four equivalent Sb(1) atoms. All Sb(1)–Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.06 Å. Te(1) is bonded to five equivalent Sm(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TeSm5 trigonal bipyramids.
